# Task and Subtask Workflow Rule

* When a new task is created, break it down into clear, actionable subtasks.
* For each subtask, create a dedicated file documenting its requirements, progress, and completion status.
* Work on only one subtask at a time. Do not start the next subtask until the current one is fully completed and documented.
* After completing a subtask, update the main task file to reflect the subtask's completion and any relevant outcomes or changes.
* Repeat this process for each subtask until the main task is fully completed.
* Ensure all task and subtask files are clearly named and organized for easy tracking and review.
